  "title": "Accountant /Senior Accountant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare/Review  full set of accounts for a group of companies and ensure all transactions are recorded properly in accordance with accounting standards and  regulations</li>\n  <li>Perform timely and accurate month-end closing and reconciliations, and ensure accounting schedules are updated accordingly</li>\n  <li>Plan monthly cash flow / budget, prepare/review payments/receipts and ensure  cash books are updated timely and accurately</li>\n  <li>Prepare/Review  the periodic management reports and conduct analytical review of the financial data</li>\n  <li>Manage all foreign exchange transactions, maintain accurate records of all foreign exchange transactions and reconcile discrepancies</li>\n  <li>Review the work of junior and peers in the accounts department, ensure day-to-day transactions are performed and recorded timely and accurately, and provide guidance as and when necessary</li>\n  <li>Ensure complete financial records filing and backups, and reinforce financial data confidentiality when necessary</li>\n  <li>Review purchase orders, sales invoices and related documents</li>\n  <li>Work closely with sales and logistics personnel to monitor and update the inventory/sales/account  receivables/account payables records</li>\n  <li>Handle the yearly audit process and ensure timely tax and statutory filing</li>\n  <li>Assist in budgeting, forecasting and analysis for operations</li>\n  <li>Assist in preparation of financial statements and disclosure notes</li>\n  <li>Communicate and sort out queries with external stakeholders, e.g. auditors, tax  agents, banks, supplier, customers, etc.</li>\n  <li>Optimise and improve internal controls and procedures</li>\n  <li>Handle  other ad-hoc tasks as assigned by supervisor</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma  / Degree in Accounting, Finance or relevant field with 5 years experience</li>\n  <li>Working  experience in audit, accounting and/or financial analysis experience, preferably in manufacturing industry</li>\n  <li>Hands-on experience with MYOB or other accounting software</li>\n  <li>Proficient  in MS Excel skills</li>\n  <li>Fluent  in speaking and writing of English, Chinese and/or Cantonese</li>\n  <li>Self-motivated, proactive in problem-solving and committed to continuous improvement</li>\n  <li>Strongattention to detail and good analytical skills</li>\n  <li>Able  to work under tight deadlines and a good team player</li>\n  <li>Frequent travel may be required</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>",
